4571/* Deallocate a socket object in response to the last Py_DECREF().
4572 First close the file description. */
4573
4574static void
4575sock_finalize(PySocketSockObject *s)
4576{
4577 SOCKET_T fd;
4578 PyObject *error_type, *error_value, *error_traceback;
4579
4580 /* Save the current exception, if any. */
4581 PyErr_Fetch(&error_type, &error_value, &error_traceback);
4582
4583 if (s->sock_fd != INVALID_SOCKET) {
4584 if (PyErr_ResourceWarning((PyObject *)s, 1, "unclosed %R", s)) {
4585 /* Spurious errors can appear at shutdown */
4586 if (PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_Warning)) {
4587 PyErr_WriteUnraisable((PyObject *)s);
4588 }
4589 }
4590
4591 /* Only close the socket *after* logging the ResourceWarning warning
4592 to allow the logger to call socket methods like
4593 socket.getsockname(). If the socket is closed before, socket
4594 methods fails with the EBADF error. */
4595 fd = s->sock_fd;
4596 s->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
4597
4598 /* We do not want to retry upon EINTR: see sock_close() */
4599 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4600 (void) SOCKETCLOSE(fd);
4601 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4602 }
4603
4604 /* Restore the saved exception. */
4605 PyErr_Restore(error_type, error_value, error_traceback);
4606}
4607
4608static void
4609sock_dealloc(PySocketSockObject *s)
4610{
4611 if (PyObject_CallFinalizerFromDealloc((PyObject *)s) < 0)
4612 return;
4613
4614 Py_TYPE(s)->tp_free((PyObject *)s);
4615}

4618static PyObject *
4619sock_repr(PySocketSockObject *s)
4620{
4621 long sock_fd;
4622 /* On Windows, this test is needed because SOCKET_T is unsigned */
4623 if (s->sock_fd == INVALID_SOCKET) {
4624 sock_fd = -1;
4625 }
4626#if SIZEOF_SOCKET_T > SIZEOF_LONG
4627 else if (s->sock_fd > LONG_MAX) {
4628 /* this can occur on Win64, and actually there is a special
4629 ugly printf formatter for decimal pointer length integer
4630 printing, only bother if necessary*/
4631 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
4632 "no printf formatter to display "
4633 "the socket descriptor in decimal");
4634 return NULL;
4635 }
4636#endif
4637 else
4638 sock_fd = (long)s->sock_fd;
4639 return PyUnicode_FromFormat(
4640 "<socket object, fd=%ld, family=%d, type=%d, proto=%d>",
4641 sock_fd, s->sock_family,
4642 s->sock_type,
4643 s->sock_proto);
4644}

4663
4664/* Initialize a new socket object. */
4665
4666#ifdef SOCK_CLOEXEC
4667/* socket() and socketpair() fail with EINVAL on Linux kernel older
4668 * than 2.6.27 if SOCK_CLOEXEC flag is set in the socket type. */
4669static int sock_cloexec_works = -1;
4670#endif
4671
4672/*ARGSUSED*/
4673static int
4674sock_initobj(PyObject *self, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
4675{
4676 PySocketSockObject *s = (PySocketSockObject *)self;
4677 PyObject *fdobj = NULL;
4678 SOCKET_T fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
4679 int family = AF_INET, type = SOCK_STREAM, proto = 0;
4680 static char *keywords[] = {"family", "type", "proto", "fileno", 0};
4681#ifndef MS_WINDOWS
4682#ifdef SOCK_CLOEXEC
4683 int *atomic_flag_works = &sock_cloexec_works;
4684#else
4685 int *atomic_flag_works = NULL;
4686#endif
4687#endif
4688
4689 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwds,
4690 "|iiiO:socket", keywords,
4691 &family, &type, &proto, &fdobj))
4692 return -1;
4693
4694 if (fdobj != NULL && fdobj != Py_None) {
4695#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
4696 /* recreate a socket that was duplicated */
4697 if (PyBytes_Check(fdobj)) {
4698 WSAPROTOCOL_INFOW info;
4699 if (PyBytes_GET_SIZE(fdobj) != sizeof(info)) {
4700 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
4701 "socket descriptor string has wrong size, "
4702 "should be %zu bytes.", sizeof(info));
4703 return -1;
4704 }
4705 memcpy(&info, PyBytes_AS_STRING(fdobj), sizeof(info));
4706 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4707 fd = WSASocketW(FROM_PROTOCOL_INFO, FROM_PROTOCOL_INFO,
4708 FROM_PROTOCOL_INFO, &info, 0, WSA_FLAG_OVERLAPPED);
4709 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4710 if (fd == INVALID_SOCKET) {
4711 set_error();
4712 return -1;
4713 }
4714 family = info.iAddressFamily;
4715 type = info.iSocketType;
4716 proto = info.iProtocol;
4717 }
4718 else
4719#endif
4720 {
4721 fd = PyLong_AsSocket_t(fdobj);
4722 if (fd == (SOCKET_T)(-1) && PyErr_Occurred())
4723 return -1;
4724 if (fd == INVALID_SOCKET) {
4725 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
4726 "can't use invalid socket value");
4727 return -1;
4728 }
4729 }
4730 }
4731 else {
4732#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
4733 /* Windows implementation */
4734#ifndef WSA_FLAG_NO_HANDLE_INHERIT
4735#define WSA_FLAG_NO_HANDLE_INHERIT 0x80
4736#endif
4737
4738 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4739 if (support_wsa_no_inherit) {
4740 fd = WSASocketW(family, type, proto,
4741 NULL, 0,
4742 WSA_FLAG_OVERLAPPED | WSA_FLAG_NO_HANDLE_INHERIT);
4743 if (fd == INVALID_SOCKET) {
4744 /* Windows 7 or Windows 2008 R2 without SP1 or the hotfix */
4745 support_wsa_no_inherit = 0;
4746 fd = socket(family, type, proto);
4747 }
4748 }
4749 else {
4750 fd = socket(family, type, proto);
4751 }
4752 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4753
4754 if (fd == INVALID_SOCKET) {
4755 set_error();
4756 return -1;
4757 }
4758
4759 if (!support_wsa_no_inherit) {
4760 if (!SetHandleInformation((HANDLE)fd, HANDLE_FLAG_INHERIT, 0)) {
4761 closesocket(fd);
4762 PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
4763 return -1;
4764 }
4765 }
4766#else
4767 /* UNIX */
4768 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4769#ifdef SOCK_CLOEXEC
4770 if (sock_cloexec_works != 0) {
4771 fd = socket(family, type | SOCK_CLOEXEC, proto);
4772 if (sock_cloexec_works == -1) {
4773 if (fd >= 0) {
4774 sock_cloexec_works = 1;
4775 }
4776 else if (errno == EINVAL) {
4777 /* Linux older than 2.6.27 does not support SOCK_CLOEXEC */
4778 sock_cloexec_works = 0;
4779 fd = socket(family, type, proto);
4780 }
4781 }
4782 }
4783 else
4784#endif
4785 {
4786 fd = socket(family, type, proto);
4787 }
4788 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4789
4790 if (fd == INVALID_SOCKET) {
4791 set_error();
4792 return -1;
4793 }
4794
4795 if (_Py_set_inheritable(fd, 0, atomic_flag_works) < 0) {
4796 SOCKETCLOSE(fd);
4797 return -1;
4798 }
4799#endif
4800 }
4801 if (init_sockobject(s, fd, family, type, proto) == -1) {
4802 SOCKETCLOSE(fd);
4803 return -1;
4804 }
4805
4806 return 0;
4807
4808}

4866/* Python interface to gethostname(). */
4867
4868/*ARGSUSED*/
4869static PyObject *
4870socket_gethostname(PyObject *self, PyObject *unused)
4871{
4872#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
4873 /* Don't use winsock's gethostname, as this returns the ANSI
4874 version of the hostname, whereas we need a Unicode string.
4875 Otherwise, gethostname apparently also returns the DNS name. */
4876 wchar_t buf[MAX_COMPUTERNAME_LENGTH + 1];
4877 DWORD size = Py_ARRAY_LENGTH(buf);
4878 wchar_t *name;
4879 PyObject *result;
4880
4881 if (GetComputerNameExW(ComputerNamePhysicalDnsHostname, buf, &size))
4882 return PyUnicode_FromWideChar(buf, size);
4883
4884 if (GetLastError() != ERROR_MORE_DATA)
4885 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
4886
4887 if (size == 0)
4888 return PyUnicode_New(0, 0);
4889
4890 /* MSDN says ERROR_MORE_DATA may occur because DNS allows longer
4891 names */
4892 name = PyMem_New(wchar_t, size);
4893 if (!name) {
4894 PyErr_NoMemory();
4895 return NULL;
4896 }
4897 if (!GetComputerNameExW(ComputerNamePhysicalDnsHostname,
4898 name,
4899 &size))
4900 {
4901 PyMem_Free(name);
4902 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
4903 }
4904
4905 result = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(name, size);
4906 PyMem_Free(name);
4907 return result;
4908#else
4909 char buf[1024];
4910 int res;
4911 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4912 res = gethostname(buf, (int) sizeof buf - 1);
4913 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4914 if (res < 0)
4915 return set_error();
4916 buf[sizeof buf - 1] = '\0';
4917 return PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault(buf);
4918#endif
4919}

5002/* Convenience function common to gethostbyname_ex and gethostbyaddr */
5003
5004static PyObject *
5005gethost_common(struct hostent *h, struct sockaddr *addr, size_t alen, int af)
5006{
5007 char **pch;
5008 PyObject *rtn_tuple = (PyObject *)NULL;
5009 PyObject *name_list = (PyObject *)NULL;
5010 PyObject *addr_list = (PyObject *)NULL;
5011 PyObject *tmp;
5012 PyObject *name;
5013
5014 if (h == NULL) {
5015 /* Let's get real error message to return */
5016 set_herror(h_errno);
5017 return NULL;
5018 }
5019
5020 if (h->h_addrtype != af) {
5021 /* Let's get real error message to return */
5022 errno = EAFNOSUPPORT;
5023 PyErr_SetFromErrno(PyExc_OSError);
5024 return NULL;
5025 }
5026
5027 switch (af) {
5028
5029 case AF_INET:
5030 if (alen < sizeof(struct sockaddr_in))
5031 return NULL;
5032 break;
5033
5034#ifdef ENABLE_IPV6
5035 case AF_INET6:
5036 if (alen < sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6))
5037 return NULL;
5038 break;
5039#endif
5040
5041 }
5042
5043 if ((name_list = PyList_New(0)) == NULL)
5044 goto err;
5045
5046 if ((addr_list = PyList_New(0)) == NULL)
5047 goto err;
5048
5049 /* SF #1511317: h_aliases can be NULL */
5050 if (h->h_aliases) {
5051 for (pch = h->h_aliases; *pch != NULL; pch++) {
5052 int status;
5053 tmp = PyUnicode_FromString(*pch);
5054 if (tmp == NULL)
5055 goto err;
5056
5057 status = PyList_Append(name_list, tmp);
5058 Py_DECREF(tmp);
5059
5060 if (status)
5061 goto err;
5062 }
5063 }
5064
5065 for (pch = h->h_addr_list; *pch != NULL; pch++) {
5066 int status;
5067
5068 switch (af) {
5069
5070 case AF_INET:
5071 {
5072 struct sockaddr_in sin;
5073 memset(&sin, 0, sizeof(sin));
5074 sin.sin_family = af;
5075#ifdef HAVE_SOCKADDR_SA_LEN
5076 sin.sin_len = sizeof(sin);
5077#endif
5078 memcpy(&sin.sin_addr, *pch, sizeof(sin.sin_addr));
5079 tmp = makeipaddr((struct sockaddr *)&sin, sizeof(sin));
5080
5081 if (pch == h->h_addr_list && alen >= sizeof(sin))
5082 memcpy((char *) addr, &sin, sizeof(sin));
5083 break;
5084 }
5085
5086#ifdef ENABLE_IPV6
5087 case AF_INET6:
5088 {
5089 struct sockaddr_in6 sin6;
5090 memset(&sin6, 0, sizeof(sin6));
5091 sin6.sin6_family = af;
5092#ifdef HAVE_SOCKADDR_SA_LEN
5093 sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(sin6);
5094#endif
5095 memcpy(&sin6.sin6_addr, *pch, sizeof(sin6.sin6_addr));
5096 tmp = makeipaddr((struct sockaddr *)&sin6,
5097 sizeof(sin6));
5098
5099 if (pch == h->h_addr_list && alen >= sizeof(sin6))
5100 memcpy((char *) addr, &sin6, sizeof(sin6));
5101 break;
5102 }
5103#endif
5104
5105 default: /* can't happen */
5106 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError,
5107 "unsupported address family");
5108 return NULL;
5109 }
5110
5111 if (tmp == NULL)
5112 goto err;
5113
5114 status = PyList_Append(addr_list, tmp);
5115 Py_DECREF(tmp);
5116
5117 if (status)
5118 goto err;
5119 }
5120
5121 name = sock_decode_hostname(h->h_name);
5122 if (name == NULL)
5123 goto err;
5124 rtn_tuple = Py_BuildValue("NOO", name, name_list, addr_list);
5125
5126 err:
5127 Py_XDECREF(name_list);
5128 Py_XDECREF(addr_list);
5129 return rtn_tuple;
5130}

5133/* Python interface to gethostbyname_ex(name). */
5134
5135/*ARGSUSED*/
5136static PyObject *
5137socket_gethostbyname_ex(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
5138{
5139 char *name;
5140 struct hostent *h;
5141 sock_addr_t addr;
5142 struct sockaddr *sa;
5143 PyObject *ret = NULL;
5144#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R
5145 struct hostent hp_allocated;
5146#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_3_ARG
5147 struct hostent_data data;
5148#else
5149 char buf[16384];
5150 int buf_len = (sizeof buf) - 1;
5151 int errnop;
5152#endif
5153#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_3_ARG
5154 int result;
5155#endif
5156#endif /* HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R */
5157
5158 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "et:gethostbyname_ex", "idna", &name))
5159 return NULL;
5160 if (setipaddr(name, SAS2SA(&addr), sizeof(addr), AF_INET) < 0)
5161 goto finally;
5162 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
5163#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R
5164#if defined(HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_6_ARG)
5165 gethostbyname_r(name, &hp_allocated, buf, buf_len,
5166 &h, &errnop);
5167#elif defined(HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_5_ARG)
5168 h = gethostbyname_r(name, &hp_allocated, buf, buf_len, &errnop);
5169#else /* HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_3_ARG */
5170 memset((void *) &data, '\0', sizeof(data));
5171 result = gethostbyname_r(name, &hp_allocated, &data);
5172 h = (result != 0) ? NULL : &hp_allocated;
5173#endif
5174#else /* not HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R */
5175#ifdef USE_GETHOSTBYNAME_LOCK
5176 PyThread_acquire_lock(netdb_lock, 1);
5177#endif
5178 SUPPRESS_DEPRECATED_CALL
5179 h = gethostbyname(name);
5180#endif /* HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R */
5181 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
5182 /* Some C libraries would require addr.__ss_family instead of
5183 addr.ss_family.
5184 Therefore, we cast the sockaddr_storage into sockaddr to
5185 access sa_family. */
5186 sa = SAS2SA(&addr);
5187 ret = gethost_common(h, SAS2SA(&addr), sizeof(addr),
5188 sa->sa_family);
5189#ifdef USE_GETHOSTBYNAME_LOCK
5190 PyThread_release_lock(netdb_lock);
5191#endif
5192finally:
5193 PyMem_Free(name);
5194 return ret;
5195}

5204/* Python interface to gethostbyaddr(IP). */
5205
5206/*ARGSUSED*/
5207static PyObject *
5208socket_gethostbyaddr(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
5209{
5210 sock_addr_t addr;
5211 struct sockaddr *sa = SAS2SA(&addr);
5212 char *ip_num;
5213 struct hostent *h;
5214 PyObject *ret = NULL;
5215#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R
5216 struct hostent hp_allocated;
5217#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_3_ARG
5218 struct hostent_data data;
5219#else
5220 /* glibcs up to 2.10 assume that the buf argument to
5221 gethostbyaddr_r is 8-byte aligned, which at least llvm-gcc
5222 does not ensure. The attribute below instructs the compiler
5223 to maintain this alignment. */
5224 char buf[16384] Py_ALIGNED(8);
5225 int buf_len = (sizeof buf) - 1;
5226 int errnop;
5227#endif
5228#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_3_ARG
5229 int result;
5230#endif
5231#endif /* HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R */
5232 char *ap;
5233 int al;
5234 int af;
5235
5236 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "et:gethostbyaddr", "idna", &ip_num))
5237 return NULL;
5238 af = AF_UNSPEC;
5239 if (setipaddr(ip_num, sa, sizeof(addr), af) < 0)
5240 goto finally;
5241 af = sa->sa_family;
5242 ap = NULL;
5243 /* al = 0; */
5244 switch (af) {
5245 case AF_INET:
5246 ap = (char *)&((struct sockaddr_in *)sa)->sin_addr;
5247 al = sizeof(((struct sockaddr_in *)sa)->sin_addr);
5248 break;
5249#ifdef ENABLE_IPV6
5250 case AF_INET6:
5251 ap = (char *)&((struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa)->sin6_addr;
5252 al = sizeof(((struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa)->sin6_addr);
5253 break;
5254#endif
5255 default:
5256 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError, "unsupported address family");
5257 goto finally;
5258 }
5259 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
5260#ifdef HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R
5261#if defined(HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_6_ARG)
5262 gethostbyaddr_r(ap, al, af,
5263 &hp_allocated, buf, buf_len,
5264 &h, &errnop);
5265#elif defined(HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_5_ARG)
5266 h = gethostbyaddr_r(ap, al, af,
5267 &hp_allocated, buf, buf_len, &errnop);
5268#else /* HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R_3_ARG */
5269 memset((void *) &data, '\0', sizeof(data));
5270 result = gethostbyaddr_r(ap, al, af, &hp_allocated, &data);
5271 h = (result != 0) ? NULL : &hp_allocated;
5272#endif
5273#else /* not HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R */
5274#ifdef USE_GETHOSTBYNAME_LOCK
5275 PyThread_acquire_lock(netdb_lock, 1);
5276#endif
5277 SUPPRESS_DEPRECATED_CALL
5278 h = gethostbyaddr(ap, al, af);
5279#endif /* HAVE_GETHOSTBYNAME_R */
5280 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
5281 ret = gethost_common(h, SAS2SA(&addr), sizeof(addr), af);
5282#ifdef USE_GETHOSTBYNAME_LOCK
5283 PyThread_release_lock(netdb_lock);
5284#endif
5285finally:
5286 PyMem_Free(ip_num);
5287 return ret;
5288}

5391#ifndef NO_DUP
5392/* dup() function for socket fds */
5393
5394static PyObject *
5395socket_dup(PyObject *self, PyObject *fdobj)
5396{
5397 SOCKET_T fd, newfd;
5398 PyObject *newfdobj;
5399#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
5400 WSAPROTOCOL_INFOW info;
5401#endif
5402
5403 fd = PyLong_AsSocket_t(fdobj);
5404 if (fd == (SOCKET_T)(-1) && PyErr_Occurred())
5405 return NULL;
5406
5407#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
5408 if (WSADuplicateSocketW(fd, GetCurrentProcessId(), &info))
5409 return set_error();
5410
5411 newfd = WSASocketW(FROM_PROTOCOL_INFO, FROM_PROTOCOL_INFO,
5412 FROM_PROTOCOL_INFO,
5413 &info, 0, WSA_FLAG_OVERLAPPED);
5414 if (newfd == INVALID_SOCKET)
5415 return set_error();
5416
5417 if (!SetHandleInformation((HANDLE)newfd, HANDLE_FLAG_INHERIT, 0)) {
5418 closesocket(newfd);
5419 PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
5420 return NULL;
5421 }
5422#else
5423 /* On UNIX, dup can be used to duplicate the file descriptor of a socket */
5424 newfd = _Py_dup(fd);
5425 if (newfd == INVALID_SOCKET)
5426 return NULL;
5427#endif
5428
5429 newfdobj = PyLong_FromSocket_t(newfd);
5430 if (newfdobj == NULL)
5431 SOCKETCLOSE(newfd);
5432 return newfdobj;
5433}

5443#ifdef HAVE_SOCKETPAIR
5444/* Create a pair of sockets using the socketpair() function.
5445 Arguments as for socket() except the default family is AF_UNIX if
5446 defined on the platform; otherwise, the default is AF_INET. */
5447
5448/*ARGSUSED*/
5449static PyObject *
5450socket_socketpair(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
5451{
5452 PySocketSockObject *s0 = NULL, *s1 = NULL;
5453 SOCKET_T sv[2];
5454 int family, type = SOCK_STREAM, proto = 0;
5455 PyObject *res = NULL;
5456#ifdef SOCK_CLOEXEC
5457 int *atomic_flag_works = &sock_cloexec_works;
5458#else
5459 int *atomic_flag_works = NULL;
5460#endif
5461 int ret;
5462
5463#if defined(AF_UNIX)
5464 family = AF_UNIX;
5465#else
5466 family = AF_INET;
5467#endif
5468 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "|iii:socketpair",
5469 &family, &type, &proto))
5470 return NULL;
5471
5472 /* Create a pair of socket fds */
5473 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
5474#ifdef SOCK_CLOEXEC
5475 if (sock_cloexec_works != 0) {
5476 ret = socketpair(family, type | SOCK_CLOEXEC, proto, sv);
5477 if (sock_cloexec_works == -1) {
5478 if (ret >= 0) {
5479 sock_cloexec_works = 1;
5480 }
5481 else if (errno == EINVAL) {
5482 /* Linux older than 2.6.27 does not support SOCK_CLOEXEC */
5483 sock_cloexec_works = 0;
5484 ret = socketpair(family, type, proto, sv);
5485 }
5486 }
5487 }
5488 else
5489#endif
5490 {
5491 ret = socketpair(family, type, proto, sv);
5492 }
5493 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
5494
5495 if (ret < 0)
5496 return set_error();
5497
5498 if (_Py_set_inheritable(sv[0], 0, atomic_flag_works) < 0)
5499 goto finally;
5500 if (_Py_set_inheritable(sv[1], 0, atomic_flag_works) < 0)
5501 goto finally;
5502
5503 s0 = new_sockobject(sv[0], family, type, proto);
5504 if (s0 == NULL)
5505 goto finally;
5506 s1 = new_sockobject(sv[1], family, type, proto);
5507 if (s1 == NULL)
5508 goto finally;
5509 res = PyTuple_Pack(2, s0, s1);
5510
5511finally:
5512 if (res == NULL) {
5513 if (s0 == NULL)
5514 SOCKETCLOSE(sv[0]);
5515 if (s1 == NULL)
5516 SOCKETCLOSE(sv[1]);
5517 }
5518 Py_XDECREF(s0);
5519 Py_XDECREF(s1);
5520 return res;
5521}

5890/* Python interface to getaddrinfo(host, port). */
5891
5892/*ARGSUSED*/
5893static PyObject *
5894socket_getaddrinfo(PyObject *self, PyObject *args, PyObject* kwargs)
5895{
5896 static char* kwnames[] = {"host", "port", "family", "type", "proto",
5897 "flags", 0};
5898 struct addrinfo hints, *res;
5899 struct addrinfo *res0 = NULL;
5900 PyObject *hobj = NULL;
5901 PyObject *pobj = (PyObject *)NULL;
5902 char pbuf[30];
5903 const char *hptr, *pptr;
5904 int family, socktype, protocol, flags;
5905 int error;
5906 PyObject *all = (PyObject *)NULL;
5907 PyObject *idna = NULL;
5908
5909 socktype = protocol = flags = 0;
5910 family = AF_UNSPEC;
5911 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwargs, "OO|iiii:getaddrinfo",
5912 kwnames, &hobj, &pobj, &family, &socktype,
5913 &protocol, &flags)) {
5914 return NULL;
5915 }
5916 if (hobj == Py_None) {
5917 hptr = NULL;
5918 } else if (PyUnicode_Check(hobj)) {
5919 idna = PyUnicode_AsEncodedString(hobj, "idna", NULL);
5920 if (!idna)
5921 return NULL;
5922 assert(PyBytes_Check(idna));
5923 hptr = PyBytes_AS_STRING(idna);
5924 } else if (PyBytes_Check(hobj)) {
5925 hptr = PyBytes_AsString(hobj);
5926 } else {
5927 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
5928 "getaddrinfo() argument 1 must be string or None");
5929 return NULL;
5930 }
5931 if (PyLong_CheckExact(pobj)) {
5932 long value = PyLong_AsLong(pobj);
5933 if (value == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
5934 goto err;
5935 PyOS_snprintf(pbuf, sizeof(pbuf), "%ld", value);
5936 pptr = pbuf;
5937 } else if (PyUnicode_Check(pobj)) {
5938 pptr = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(pobj);
5939 if (pptr == NULL)
5940 goto err;
5941 } else if (PyBytes_Check(pobj)) {
5942 pptr = PyBytes_AS_STRING(pobj);
5943 } else if (pobj == Py_None) {
5944 pptr = (char *)NULL;
5945 } else {
5946 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError, "Int or String expected");
5947 goto err;
5948 }
5949#if defined(__APPLE__) && defined(AI_NUMERICSERV)
5950 if ((flags & AI_NUMERICSERV) && (pptr == NULL || (pptr[0] == '0' && pptr[1] == 0))) {
5951 /* On OSX upto at least OSX 10.8 getaddrinfo crashes
5952 * if AI_NUMERICSERV is set and the servname is NULL or "0".
5953 * This workaround avoids a segfault in libsystem.
5954 */
5955 pptr = "00";
5956 }
5957#endif
5958 memset(&hints, 0, sizeof(hints));
5959 hints.ai_family = family;
5960 hints.ai_socktype = socktype;
5961 hints.ai_protocol = protocol;
5962 hints.ai_flags = flags;
5963 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
5964 ACQUIRE_GETADDRINFO_LOCK
5965 error = getaddrinfo(hptr, pptr, &hints, &res0);
5966 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
5967 RELEASE_GETADDRINFO_LOCK /* see comment in setipaddr() */
5968 if (error) {
5969 set_gaierror(error);
5970 goto err;
5971 }
5972
5973 all = PyList_New(0);
5974 if (all == NULL)
5975 goto err;
5976 for (res = res0; res; res = res->ai_next) {
5977 PyObject *single;
5978 PyObject *addr =
5979 makesockaddr(-1, res->ai_addr, res->ai_addrlen, protocol);
5980 if (addr == NULL)
5981 goto err;
5982 single = Py_BuildValue("iiisO", res->ai_family,
5983 res->ai_socktype, res->ai_protocol,
5984 res->ai_canonname ? res->ai_canonname : "",
5985 addr);
5986 Py_DECREF(addr);
5987 if (single == NULL)
5988 goto err;
5989
5990 if (PyList_Append(all, single))
5991 goto err;
5992 Py_XDECREF(single);
5993 }
5994 Py_XDECREF(idna);
5995 if (res0)
5996 freeaddrinfo(res0);
5997 return all;
5998 err:
5999 Py_XDECREF(all);
6000 Py_XDECREF(idna);
6001 if (res0)
6002 freeaddrinfo(res0);
6003 return (PyObject *)NULL;
6004}

6012/* Python interface to getnameinfo(sa, flags). */
6013
6014/*ARGSUSED*/
6015static PyObject *
6016socket_getnameinfo(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
6017{
6018 PyObject *sa = (PyObject *)NULL;
6019 int flags;
6020 char *hostp;
6021 int port;
6022 unsigned int flowinfo, scope_id;
6023 char hbuf[NI_MAXHOST], pbuf[NI_MAXSERV];
6024 struct addrinfo hints, *res = NULL;
6025 int error;
6026 PyObject *ret = (PyObject *)NULL;
6027 PyObject *name;
6028
6029 flags = flowinfo = scope_id = 0;
6030 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "Oi:getnameinfo", &sa, &flags))
6031 return NULL;
6032 if (!PyTuple_Check(sa)) {
6033 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
6034 "getnameinfo() argument 1 must be a tuple");
6035 return NULL;
6036 }
6037 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(sa, "si|II;getnameinfo(): illegal sockaddr argument",
6038 &hostp, &port, &flowinfo, &scope_id))
6039 {
6040 return NULL;
6041 }
6042 if (flowinfo > 0xfffff) {
6043 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
6044 "getnameinfo(): flowinfo must be 0-1048575.");
6045 return NULL;
6046 }
6047 PyOS_snprintf(pbuf, sizeof(pbuf), "%d", port);
6048 memset(&hints, 0, sizeof(hints));
6049 hints.ai_family = AF_UNSPEC;
6050 hints.ai_socktype = SOCK_DGRAM; /* make numeric port happy */
6051 hints.ai_flags = AI_NUMERICHOST; /* don't do any name resolution */
6052 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
6053 ACQUIRE_GETADDRINFO_LOCK
6054 error = getaddrinfo(hostp, pbuf, &hints, &res);
6055 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
6056 RELEASE_GETADDRINFO_LOCK /* see comment in setipaddr() */
6057 if (error) {
6058 set_gaierror(error);
6059 goto fail;
6060 }
6061 if (res->ai_next) {
6062 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError,
6063 "sockaddr resolved to multiple addresses");
6064 goto fail;
6065 }
6066 switch (res->ai_family) {
6067 case AF_INET:
6068 {
6069 if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(sa) != 2) {
6070 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError,
6071 "IPv4 sockaddr must be 2 tuple");
6072 goto fail;
6073 }
6074 break;
6075 }
6076#ifdef ENABLE_IPV6
6077 case AF_INET6:
6078 {
6079 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
6080 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)res->ai_addr;
6081 sin6->sin6_flowinfo = htonl(flowinfo);
6082 sin6->sin6_scope_id = scope_id;
6083 break;
6084 }
6085#endif
6086 }
6087 error = getnameinfo(res->ai_addr, (socklen_t) res->ai_addrlen,
6088 hbuf, sizeof(hbuf), pbuf, sizeof(pbuf), flags);
6089 if (error) {
6090 set_gaierror(error);
6091 goto fail;
6092 }
6093
6094 name = sock_decode_hostname(hbuf);
6095 if (name == NULL)
6096 goto fail;
6097 ret = Py_BuildValue("Ns", name, pbuf);
6098
6099fail:
6100 if (res)
6101 freeaddrinfo(res);
6102 return ret;
6103}

6174 for (i = 0; ni[i].if_index != 0 && i < INT_MAX; i++) {
6175 PyObject *ni_tuple = Py_BuildValue("IO&",
6176 ni[i].if_index, PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault, ni[i].if_name);
6177
6178 if (ni_tuple == NULL || PyList_Append(list, ni_tuple) == -1) {
6179 Py_XDECREF(ni_tuple);
6180 Py_DECREF(list);
6181 if_freenameindex(ni);
6182 return NULL;
6183 }
6184 Py_DECREF(ni_tuple);
6185 }
6186
6187 if_freenameindex(ni);
6188 return list;
6189}

6191PyDoc_STRVAR(if_nameindex_doc,
6192"if_nameindex()\n\
6193\n\
6194Returns a list of network interface information (index, name) tuples.");
6195
6196static PyObject *
6197socket_if_nametoindex(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
6198{
6199 PyObject *oname;
6200 unsigned long index;
6201
6202 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O&:if_nametoindex",
6203 PyUnicode_FSConverter, &oname))
6204 return NULL;
6205
6206 index = if_nametoindex(PyBytes_AS_STRING(oname));
6207 Py_DECREF(oname);
6208 if (index == 0) {
6209 /* if_nametoindex() doesn't set errno */
6210 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError, "no interface with this name");
6211 return NULL;
6212 }
6213
6214 return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong(index);
6215}

6387
6388/* Additional initialization and cleanup for Windows */
6389
6390static void
6391os_cleanup(void)
6392{
6393 WSACleanup();
6394}
6395
6396static int
6397os_init(void)
6398{
6399 WSADATA WSAData;
6400 int ret;
6401 ret = WSAStartup(0x0101, &WSAData);
6402 switch (ret) {
6403 case 0: /* No error */
6404 Py_AtExit(os_cleanup);
6405 return 1; /* Success */
6406 case WSASYSNOTREADY:
6407 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ImportError,
6408 "WSAStartup failed: network not ready");
6409 break;
6410 case WSAVERNOTSUPPORTED:
6411 case WSAEINVAL:
6412 PyErr_SetString(
6413 PyExc_ImportError,
6414 "WSAStartup failed: requested version not supported");
6415 break;
6416 default:
6417 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ImportError, "WSAStartup failed: error code %d", ret);
6418 break;
6419 }
6420 return 0; /* Failure */
6421}
6422
6423#endif /* MS_WINDOWS */

6447/* Initialize the _socket module.
6448
6449 This module is actually called "_socket", and there's a wrapper
6450 "socket.py" which implements some additional functionality.
6451 The import of "_socket" may fail with an ImportError exception if
6452 os-specific initialization fails. On Windows, this does WINSOCK
6453 initialization. When WINSOCK is initialized successfully, a call to
6454 WSACleanup() is scheduled to be made at exit time.
6455*/
6456
6457PyDoc_STRVAR(socket_doc,
6458"Implementation module for socket operations.\n\
6459\n\
6460See the socket module for documentation.");
6461
6462static struct PyModuleDef socketmodule = {
6463 PyModuleDef_HEAD_INIT,
6464 PySocket_MODULE_NAME,
6465 socket_doc,
6466 -1,
6467 socket_methods,
6468 NULL,
6469 NULL,
6470 NULL,
6471 NULL
6472};

6474PyMODINIT_FUNC
6475PyInit__socket(void)
6476{
6477 PyObject *m, *has_ipv6;
6478
6479 if (!os_init())
6480 return NULL;
6481
6482#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
6483 if (support_wsa_no_inherit == -1) {
6484#if defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1800
6485 support_wsa_no_inherit = IsWindows7SP1OrGreater();
6486#else
6487 DWORD version = GetVersion();
6488 DWORD major = (DWORD)LOBYTE(LOWORD(version));
6489 DWORD minor = (DWORD)HIBYTE(LOWORD(version));
6490 /* need Windows 7 SP1, 2008 R2 SP1 or later */
6491 support_wsa_no_inherit = major > 6 || (major == 6 && minor >= 1);
6492#endif
6493 }
6494#endif
6495
6496 Py_TYPE(&sock_type) = &PyType_Type;
6497 m = PyModule_Create(&socketmodule);
6498 if (m == NULL)
6499 return NULL;
6500
6501 Py_INCREF(PyExc_OSError);
6502 PySocketModuleAPI.error = PyExc_OSError;
6503 Py_INCREF(PyExc_OSError);
6504 PyModule_AddObject(m, "error", PyExc_OSError);
6505 socket_herror = PyErr_NewException("socket.herror",
6506 PyExc_OSError, NULL);
6507 if (socket_herror == NULL)
6508 return NULL;
6509 Py_INCREF(socket_herror);
6510 PyModule_AddObject(m, "herror", socket_herror);
6511 socket_gaierror = PyErr_NewException("socket.gaierror", PyExc_OSError,
6512 NULL);
6513 if (socket_gaierror == NULL)
6514 return NULL;
6515 Py_INCREF(socket_gaierror);
6516 PyModule_AddObject(m, "gaierror", socket_gaierror);
6517 socket_timeout = PyErr_NewException("socket.timeout",
6518 PyExc_OSError, NULL);
6519 if (socket_timeout == NULL)
6520 return NULL;
6521 PySocketModuleAPI.timeout_error = socket_timeout;
6522 Py_INCREF(socket_timeout);
6523 PyModule_AddObject(m, "timeout", socket_timeout);
6524 Py_INCREF((PyObject *)&sock_type);
6525 if (PyModule_AddObject(m, "SocketType",
6526 (PyObject *)&sock_type) != 0)
6527 return NULL;
6528 Py_INCREF((PyObject *)&sock_type);
6529 if (PyModule_AddObject(m, "socket",
6530 (PyObject *)&sock_type) != 0)
6531 return NULL;
6532
6533#ifdef ENABLE_IPV6
6534 has_ipv6 = Py_True;
6535#else
6536 has_ipv6 = Py_False;
6537#endif
6538 Py_INCREF(has_ipv6);
6539 PyModule_AddObject(m, "has_ipv6", has_ipv6);
6540
6541 /* Export C API */
6542 if (PyModule_AddObject(m, PySocket_CAPI_NAME,
6543 PyCapsule_New(&PySocketModuleAPI, PySocket_CAPSULE_NAME, NULL)
6544 ) != 0)
6545 return NULL;

7643#if defined(SIO_LOOPBACK_FAST_PATH)

7645#endif

7654 }
7655 }
